CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 3, 1953, pg. 5, reads: "George Gaines Gives Annual Christmas Party - George Gaines, Grand Master of Pennsylvania Masons and East Liberty Mortician, who gives an annual Christmas party for the youngsters of the city, repeated his annual give-away fete this year. Each child, after being entertained with a wonderful party, was sent home with a bag of goodies and a toy. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of children, including girl standing on right wearing floral cardigan, dark pleated skirt, and holding stocking, gathered around Christmas tree in Gaines Funeral Chapel for annual Christmas party
